description.plain:
Devin Copeland (born June 4, 1970), better known by his stage name Devin the Dude, is an American rapper from Houston, Texas.

Early in his career, he was part of the influential underground group the Odd Squad with the legendary DJ Screw.

He released has debut solo album, The Dude in 1998, with a laid back flow and frequent references to sex and weed.

This album attracted the attention of Dr. Dre, who featured him on the song “Fuck You” from his album 2001, giving Devin national exposure.

description.plain: Devin the Dude’s corpus of work features themes about romantic discontent, having game, offending parents, police brutality, drinking beer, and smoking weed.  Many songs include humor, as Devin the Dude impersonates various personas in "Cultural Coughee," "Twilla," "Yee Haw," or makes social commentary in "Almighty Dollar," or employs light humor in songs like "She Useta Be" or "She Want that Money."  Although the benefits and uses of marijuana dominate his lyrical content, several songs give listeners more access to rap as an industry and occupation.  This song, similar to "I Need a Song," exemplifies the sincere struggles that go into making the music that we hear.
